How to implement a new integration test?
* Maven configuration
Add at least the following Maven dependencies on your test case POM project:
<dependency>
	<groupId>org.societies.integration.test.util</groupId>
	<artifactId>integrationtestutil</artifactId>
	<version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
	<scope>compile</scope>
</dependency>
<dependency>
	<groupId>junit</groupId>
	<artifactId>junit</artifactId>
	<version>4.0</version>
	<scope>compile</scope>
</dependency>
	
* Test Case Creation
Create a Java class to extend "IntegrationTestCase"
You only have to extend the default constructor as follow
public YourTestCase() {
	// Call the super constructor
	super();
	// Define the test case number, and test classes to launch
	testCaseNumber = 759;
	testCaseClasses = new Class[]{YourNominalTestCase.class, YourSpecificTestCase.class};
}

And to create your test case classes "YourNominalTestCase" and "YourSpecificTestCase" using the jUnit tool.

* Virgo configuration
Then your need to launch the "run" method of this class. This can be done automatically through Virgo:
init-method="run"